# {domain} Workspace — AI Bootstrap Rules

## Scope
- Treat this workspace root as a multi-repo shell, not as a single Git repository.
- Detect repository folders before writing repo-local agent files.
- Use [.ai/memory/workspace-map.json](.ai/memory/workspace-map.json) as the live workspace inventory.

## Source Of Truth
- `.github/agents/` — canonical agent definitions (Copilot workspace agents)
- `.github/skills/` — canonical skills
- `.github/prompts/` — canonical prompt entry points
- `.ai/memory/` — machine-generated bootstrap inventory (workspace-map.json, mcp-registry.json)

`.ai/` exists only for bootstrap operational memory. All authored assets live in `.github/`.

## Domain
- Name: {name}
- Domain: {domain}
- Stack: {stack}
- Java package: {package}
- Repositories: {repos}

## Workspace Rules
- Use this root `AGENTS.md` as the only workspace-wide instruction file for Copilot in VS Code.
- Do not duplicate the same workspace instructions into `.github/copilot-instructions.md`.
- Agents are authored directly in `.github/agents/`. Other adapters copy from there — never the reverse.
- Preserve existing repo-local agent files and treat them as authoritative for their own repository.
- After each bootstrap implementation or bootstrap review, update `AI_BOOTSTRAP_IMPROVEMENTS.md`.

## Detection Contract
1. Scan the workspace root for `.claude/`, `.cursor/`, `.github/`, `.gemini/`.
2. Detect active processes: `cursor`, `claude`, `code`, `node`.
3. Classify the runtime as `IDE`, `TERMINAL`, or `HYBRID`.
4. Classify top-level folders as Git repositories or utility folders.
5. Emit this JSON payload before making bootstrap decisions:

```json
{
  "mode": "IDE | TERMINAL | HYBRID",
  "primary_tool": "cursor | claude | copilot | gemini | codex",
  "secondary_tools": []
}
```

## Adapter Policy
- Copilot: keep `AGENTS.md` at root, expose custom assets through `.github/agents/`, `.github/prompts/`, `.github/skills/`.
- Claude: use `CLAUDE.md` as an alias to `AGENTS.md`; keep `.claude/agents/` as baseline adapter.
- Gemini: keep `.gemini/antigravity/agents/` as baseline adapter.

## MCP Policy
- Read [.vscode/mcp.json](.vscode/mcp.json) before proposing new MCP servers.
- Reuse existing MCPs first: `bitbucket-corporate`, `oracle-official`.
- Do not add new MCP servers unless built-in capabilities are insufficient.

## Safety
- Never assume every repository should inherit workspace-level adapters automatically.
- Do not overwrite existing repo-local CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or .github assets unless explicitly requested.
